scheduled_activities.description: Explore a gentle, yet powerful series of postures and breathing techniques that promote physical strength, flexibility, and mental clarity. Whether you are a beginner or an experienced practitioner, Hatha Yoga offers a balanced approach to cultivate inner peace, enhance mindfulness, and restore harmony to your being. Join us and experience the transformative benefits of Hatha Yoga for overall well-being and vitality.

Get prepared to get energized and sweat to the beat of the music through high intensity interval training (H.I.I.T) and tempo segments. This workout will feature different positions on the spin bike to utilize different muscle compartments for a more overall body workout. Lights off, Sweat on!

Inspired by elements of ballet, yoga, and Pilates, this class focuses on low-impact, high-intensity movements designed to strengthen your body and give you long lean muscles. You’ll use low-weight and high repetitions. No dance experience required.

Work at your own pace as your instructor takes you through a series of both strength training and cardio full body movements that’ll have you sweating and your muscles burning. With a variety of exercises in each session you will leave feeling strong and accomplished!

Challenge yourself with this great cardio conditioning class! Instructors will lead you through a variety of challenging rides including hills, sprints and team riding all set to great motivating music. Suitable for all levels of riders.

Aquafit is a dynamic full-body workout that combines the power of water-resistance with targeted exercises to enhance your strength. Led by our instructors to music, this 45-minute session takes place in shallow-water, providing an enviornment that challenges your muscles while being gentle on your joints.

Yin Yoga targets your deep connective tissues, like your fascia, ligaments, joints, and bones. In this class, movements are slower and held for longer periods of time, which will help you stretch and lengthen tight tissues, while also teaching you how to breathe through discomfort and sit with your thoughts.

Core. Cardio. Strength. This workout is designed to target all major muscles groups. Work towards a healthier mind and body as you stay active during your week with this energetic class. No matter your experience or fitness level this class is for you.

Discover varying terrains while riding along to a unique playlist. Each instructor brings a different style to their class to give you a different challenge each ride. Cycle Fit is meant to make you sweat, increase your heart rate and have fun! Perfect for new and advanced riders.

Aquafit is a dynamic full-body workout that combines the power of water-resistance with targeted exercises to enhance your strength. Led by our instructors to music, this 45-minute session takes place in shallow-water, providing an enviornment that challenges your muscles while being gentle on your joints.

This workout uses resistance training with high repetitions to activate fast twitch muscle fibers. You will grow strong, lean muscle mass and enhance your athleticism. The calorie burn won’t just stop after the class is over - your lean muscle fibers will keep you burning calories for long after you’ve left!
Interfaith Chaplain Erin will lead us through times of movement, stillness, contemplation, and reflection as we ground ourselves in nature. This is a great opportunity for intention and connection!

Do you do allyship or equity-focused work on campus or hope to this year? This type of work can take a lot of emotional labour. Self-care is extra important in being an effective ally.
